# Pitolet Cloud — production environment. Copy to `.env` and fill in.
# `.env` holds secrets — never commit it.

# ---- image ----
# Which published image tag to run (matches the GitHub deploy workflow input).
TAG=latest

# ---- postgres (compose service `postgres`) ----
POSTGRES_DB=pitolet
POSTGRES_USER=pitolet
# Strong random password: openssl rand -hex 24
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=change-me

# ---- app (apps/cloud/src/server.ts) ----
# Must match the postgres service name/creds above. Host is the compose
# service name `postgres`, port 5432.
DATABASE_URL=postgres://pitolet:change-me@postgres:5432/pitolet
# Session-signing secret for better-auth: openssl rand -hex 32
BETTER_AUTH_SECRET=change-me
# Public origin of the app — used for cookies, magic links, OAuth callbacks.
BETTER_AUTH_URL=https://app.pitolet.com

# ---- monitoring (see README.md "Monitoring") ----
# Shared secret gating GET /internal/metrics. Unset = endpoint 404s (off).
# Generate: openssl rand -hex 32. Then:
#   curl -H "Authorization: Bearer <token>" https://app.pitolet.com/internal/metrics
# PITOLET_METRICS_TOKEN=
# Optional error tracking. Any Sentry-DSN-compatible backend (Sentry, GlitchTip).
# Requires installing the optional package in the image: pnpm add @sentry/node.
# SENTRY_DSN=

# ---- optional integrations ----
# Transactional email (magic links) — https://resend.com
# RESEND_API_KEY=
# OAuth sign-in providers (leave unset to disable):
# GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=
# GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=

# ---- backups (compose service `backup`, restic) ----
# Hetzner Storage Box over sftp, e.g.
#   sftp:u123456@u123456.your-storagebox.de:/backups/pitolet
RESTIC_REPOSITORY=sftp:USER@USER.your-storagebox.de:/pitolet
# Encryption password for the restic repo: openssl rand -hex 32
# Store this somewhere safe OFF the VPS — without it backups are unrecoverable.
RESTIC_PASSWORD=change-me
